rinters|location=Chennai, India|year=1993}}</ref><ref name=\"Garg\">{{cite book|title=Encyclopaedia of the Hindu World: Ak-Aq|url=https://books.google.com/?id=WjDcd0cTFxQC&pg=PA352&dq=poygai#v=onepage&q=poygai&f=false|pages=352\u2013354|publisher=Concept Publishing Company|last=Garg|first=Ga\u1e45g\u0101 R\u0101m|year=1992|isbn=9788170223757}}</ref>\n|-\n|43\n|[[Varadharaja Perumal Temple, Kanchipuram|Thirukkachi - Atthigiri]]\n|[[Kanchipuram]],<br> [[Kanchipuram district]], <br>[[Tamil Nadu]]{{coord|12.819137| 79.724646}}\n|[[File:Varadaraja Perumal Temple Kanchipuram (31).jpg|130px|center]] \n|Sri Perundevi sametha Sri Devadiraja Perumal\n|One of the greatest Hindu scholars of Vaishnava [[VisishtAdvaita]] philosophy, [[Ramanuja]] is believed to have resided in this temple.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.indiantemples.com/Tamilnadu/varakanc.html |title = The Templenet Encyclopedia - Varadaraja Perumal Temple at Kanchipuram}}</ref> The temple along with [[Ekambareswarar Temple (Kanchipuram)|Ekambareswarar Temple]] and [[Kamakshi Amman Temple]] in Kanchipuram is popularly known as  ''Mumurtivasam'' (abode of trio),<ref name=\"Rao154\">Rao 2008, p. 154</ref> while Srirangam is referred to as \u2018 The Koil\u2019 (meaning: \"temple\") and [[Venkateswara Temple, Tirumala|Tirupati]] as the \u2018Malai\u2019 (Meaning: \"hill\").\n|-\n|44\n|[[Ashtabujakaram|Ashtabuyagaram]]\n|[[Kanchipuram]],<br> [[Kanchipuram district]], <br>[[Tamil Nadu]]{{coord|12.822736| 79.710806}}\n|[[File:Ashtabhujakaram (9).jpg|130px|center]] \n|Sri Padmasani sametha Sri Ashtabhuja Perumal\n|\n|-\n|45\n|[[Tiruththanka|Thiruthanka]]\n|[[Kanchipuram]],<br> [[Kanchipuram district]], <br>[[Tamil Nadu]]{{coord|12.824382| 79.705543}}\n|[[File:Vilakkoli-perumal108dd.jpg|130px|center]] \n|Sri Maragadhavalli sametha Sri Deepaprakasa Perumal\n|\n|-\n|46\n|[[Tiruvelukkai|Thiruvelukkai]]\n|[[Kanchipuram]],<br> [[Kanchipuram district]], <br>[[Tamil Nadu]]{{coord|12.822197| 79.706450}}\n|[[File:Tiruvelukkai (