{"title_page": "List of chuches in the Roman Catholic Diocese of Sacramento", "text_new": "This is a list of current and former [[Roman Catholicism in the United States|Roman Catholic]] churches in the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Sacramento]]. The diocese consists of 12 deaneries covering 20 counties in the northwest portion of [[California]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Diocese of Sacramento 2019 Directory|publisher=Diocese of Sacramento|year=2019|accessdate=April 20, 2020|url=https://www.scd.org/sites/default/files/2019-10/SCD-Directory-Rev11.pdf}}</ref> The Diocese is headquartered at the [[Cathedral of the Blessed Sacrament in Sacramento|Cathedral of the Blessed Sacrament]] in [[Sacramento, California]].\n\n==American River Deanery==\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:75%\"\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"25%\" |'''Name'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"10%\" |'''Image'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"25%\" |'''Location'''\n! style=\"background:darkviolet; color:yellow;\" width=\"15\" |'''Description/Notes'''\n|-\n|Our Lady of the Assumpton\n|\n|5057 Cottage Way, [[Carmichael, California|Carmichael]]\n|1952\n|-\n|Our Lady of Lourdes\n|\n|1951 North Ave, Sacramento\n|1957\n|-\n|Presentation of the Blessed Virgin Mary\n|\n|4123 Robertson Ave, Sacramento\n|1961\n|-\n|St. Ignatius Loyola\n|\n|3235 Arden Way, Sacramento\n|1954\n|-\n|St. John the Evangelist\n|\n|5751 Locust Ave, Carmichael\n|1960\n|-\n|St. John Vianney\n|\n|10497 Coloma Rd, [[Rancho Cordova, California|Rancho Cordova]]\n|1958\n|-\n|St. Joseph\n|\n|1717 El Monte Ave, Sacramento\n|1924\n|-\n|St. Lawrence\n|\n|4325 Don Julio Blvd, [[North Highlands, California|North Highlands]]\n|1955\n|-\n|St. Mel\n|\n|4745 Pennsylvania Ave, [[Fair Oaks, California|Fair Oaks]]\n|1947\n|-\n|St. Philomene\n|\n|2428 Bell St, Sacramento\n|1948\n|}\n\n==City Deanery==\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:75%\"\n! style=\"backgro